          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Apply with a new lender (through Nik Finance, one application compared against 130+ lenders)</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">New lender assesses your current financial situation, credit history, and vehicle details</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">If approved, the new lender pays out your existing loan in full</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">PPSR security registration transfers from old lender to new lender</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">You begin repayments to the new lender at the new rate</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The whole process typically takes 1–2 weeks from application to settlement.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">When Refinancing Makes Sense</h2>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Your Credit Has Improved</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Extremely common — many borrowers initially finance through a dealer or specialist lender at a higher rate. After 12–24 months of consistent repayments, your credit score improves and you may qualify for a significantly lower rate from a mainstream lender.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">You Took Dealer Finance</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Dealer finance often carries rates 2–4% higher than independent options because the dealer earns commission on the rate. If you did not compare options at the time, it is worth checking now.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Market Rates Have Dropped</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The RBA cash rate has moved significantly over recent years. If you locked in during a higher rate period, better options may exist. The current cash rate is 3.85% following the February 2026 increase.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Your Situation Has Changed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Whether you want lower monthly repayments (extend the term) or to pay off faster (maintain repayments at a lower rate), refinancing gives you flexibility.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Costs and Break-Even Analysis</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Check whether your current loan has early exit fees (many modern car loans do not). The new lender may charge an establishment fee, though many waive this for refinancing.</p>
        <div class="bg-[#0d4d3e]/5 border-l-4 border-[#10b981] rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6"><p class="text-[#0d4d3e] font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Simple break-even example: if switching costs are $300 and you save $60/month, you break even in 5 months — every month after that is pure savings. We calculate this for you and only recommend refinancing if it genuinely saves money after all costs.</p></div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Even moving from 10% to 8% on a $25,000 balance over 3 remaining years saves approximately $780 in interest.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Refinancing After a Bad Credit Car Loan</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">One of the most powerful opportunities. If you took a loan at 14–18% because your credit was impaired and have since made 12–24 months of consistent repayments, your credit profile has likely improved significantly. You may now qualify for 8–12% or lower.</p>
        <div class="bg-[#0d4d3e]/5 border-l-4 border-[#10b981] rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6"><p class="text-[#0d4d3e] font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">On a $20,000 balance with 3 years remaining, dropping from 15% to 9% saves approximately $1,900 in interest and reduces monthly repayments by about $53.</p></div>
      </section>
